  "summary": "Capesize\nA positive end to the week as BHP Billiton fixed a 17 September onwards 170,000 tonne 10% cargo from Port Hedland to Qingdao at $4.80 and $4.90. Rio Tinto having fixed overnight at $4.55 for Dampier has also now paid $4.80. Timecharter rates were also firmer with 180,000 tonnes now fixing around the mid $8,000 daily range for round voyages to the East.",
